HEADWORD: mandril
<hw>mandril</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>any of various shafts that rotate or
serve as axes for larger rotating parts.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>manderil</asp> and <asp>mandrel</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> spindle, mandrel, arbor.</syn>⟦br⟧
